1. THE OPTIMAL WORKFLOW (STEP‑BY‑STEP)

STEP 1 — User opens the repo (iPad or Desktop)

The user—not Copilot—accesses:

[github.com/simeyron/Legal-Calculus](http://github.com/simeyron/Legal-Calculus)

They choose a file or artifact to work on.

---

STEP 2 — User brings the content into Copilot Pro

Because Copilot cannot fetch files, the user:

- copies the text from GitHub
• or downloads/uploads the file
• or pastes a section they want analyzed

This is the only way content enters Copilot.

---

STEP 3 — Copilot Pro becomes the “thinking engine”

Once the content is pasted, Copilot Pro can:

- analyze doctrine
• rewrite modules
• structure arguments
• build timelines
• map Educate → Build → Challenge
• generate curriculum
• stress‑test reasoning
• create Blueprint AI workflows

This is where Copilot Pro is uniquely strong: long reasoning, structured logic, multi‑layer analysis.

---

STEP 4 — User decides what goes back into the repo

Copilot never commits.

The user:

- reviews the output
• revises it
• decides what is correct
• copies it back into GitHub
• commits the change

This preserves:

- authorship
• transparency
• procedural integrity
• human control

This is the DECIDE phase of the Shield Protocol.

---

STEP 5 — Iterate

The user repeats:

EDUCATE → BUILD → CHALLENGE → DECIDE

Each cycle improves:

- clarity
• structure
• reasoning
• evidence alignment
• procedural literacy

This is how Legal‑Calculus grows as a living archive.

